1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:42,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:43,148 --> 00:00:48,070
CHAPTER 19:
YOU JUST HAVE SUCH GOOD CHEMISTRY

3
00:00:50,197 --> 00:00:52,783
EPISODE 6

4
00:00:53,826 --> 00:00:55,619
This can't be real.

5
00:00:55,703 --> 00:00:56,912
It's just a dream.

6
00:00:56,996 --> 00:00:59,415
There's no way this is really happening.

7
00:00:59,498 --> 00:01:00,916
It just can't be.

8
00:01:04,670 --> 00:01:07,339
I just want to die.

9
00:01:07,423 --> 00:01:10,759
Why did it have to be him?

10
00:01:10,843 --> 00:01:12,845
I'm so embarrassed.

11
00:01:12,928 --> 00:01:14,722
This is so humiliating.

12
00:01:15,681 --> 00:01:18,309
Why is he still reading?

13
00:01:20,311 --> 00:01:21,812
Is he enjoying it?

14
00:01:23,314 --> 00:01:24,148
What?

15
00:01:24,857 --> 00:01:25,691
Sorry?

16
00:01:26,650 --> 00:01:27,651
What!

17
00:01:37,369 --> 00:01:40,539
He's supposed to be a genius.
Is he a genius at torture too?

18
00:01:40,623 --> 00:01:43,125
Making me die of humiliation
without a single visible wound?

19
00:01:52,301 --> 00:01:54,136
-Yeo Eui-ju.
-Yes, sir?

20
00:01:55,346 --> 00:01:56,555
What's this?

21
00:01:56,639 --> 00:01:57,473
Sorry, sir?

22
00:02:01,894 --> 00:02:03,145
I asked what this is.

23
00:02:08,776 --> 00:02:09,818
The thing is.

24
00:02:10,611 --> 00:02:13,989
It looks like someone
was working on a web novel.

25
00:02:15,449 --> 00:02:16,992
-Indeed.
-Yes.

26
00:02:17,952 --> 00:02:19,536
Yes, well.

27
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:22,456
I was pretty surprised myself.

28
00:02:22,539 --> 00:02:24,208
Gosh, that's just nasty…

29
00:02:25,084 --> 00:02:26,168
It's not yours?

30
00:02:26,251 --> 00:02:27,086
No, sir.

31
00:02:27,878 --> 00:02:29,046
I didn't write it.

32
00:02:29,129 --> 00:02:31,590
Like someone who admits to drinking
but denies drunk driving.

33
00:02:32,216 --> 00:02:34,593
You've been caught red-handed,
yet you deny it?

34
00:02:38,681 --> 00:02:41,600
The clueless Korean lit. major Choi Yoon
is Dong-ju.

35
00:02:41,684 --> 00:02:43,102
The complete asshole…

36
00:02:46,814 --> 00:02:48,315
of a math genius Ju Si-on is me.

37
00:02:49,358 --> 00:02:50,943
The dumb sports major Kang Tae-ha,

38
00:02:51,026 --> 00:02:53,529
who solves everything with force,
is Gi-jeon.

39
00:02:53,612 --> 00:02:56,490
And Han Jae-min,
who comes from Japan and is loaded,

40
00:02:57,282 --> 00:02:58,117
is Da-ju.

41
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:02,079
No.

42
00:03:02,162 --> 00:03:04,081
How did you come to that conclusion?

43
00:03:06,417 --> 00:03:08,085
"I didn't realize
you were such a lost cause."

44
00:03:08,168 --> 00:03:09,003
"I'm very disappointed."

45
00:03:09,086 --> 00:03:10,879
"It was clearly your fault
and you've admitted it."

46
00:03:10,963 --> 00:03:12,464
"All that's left is compensation."

47
00:03:12,548 --> 00:03:15,009
"Breaking my glasses caused
ten million won's worth of damage."

48
00:03:15,092 --> 00:03:17,011
"You'll have to find another way
to repay me."

49
00:03:18,929 --> 00:03:21,807
All that being word for word what I said
is a coincidence?

50
00:03:25,019 --> 00:03:27,396
"You wouldn't let him sleep.
Don't you know he's a sleepyhead?"

51
00:03:27,479 --> 00:03:29,690
Da-ju said that in the car
on the way to school.

52
00:03:29,773 --> 00:03:31,066
Is this all just a coincidence?

53
00:03:31,442 --> 00:03:33,569
Or is my imagination running wild?

54
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:36,613
You just have such good chemistry.

55
00:03:38,866 --> 00:03:39,783
What?

56
00:03:39,867 --> 00:03:41,410
You all have such good chemistry.

57
00:03:41,493 --> 00:03:43,162
So I just wrote about it.

58
00:03:43,245 --> 00:03:44,163
But the thing is…

59
00:03:44,246 --> 00:03:46,790
People really liked it, so…

60
00:03:50,127 --> 00:03:52,588
Even if you can't tell
right from wrong, still…

61
00:03:52,671 --> 00:03:54,506
There's a line you shouldn't cross.

62
00:03:55,632 --> 00:03:56,717
I'm sorry.

63
00:03:57,468 --> 00:03:58,635
Delete it.

64
00:04:00,304 --> 00:04:01,221
Sorry?

65
00:04:02,598 --> 00:04:03,515
I can't, sir.

66
00:04:04,308 --> 00:04:05,142
You can't?

67
00:04:07,019 --> 00:04:08,145
No, I can't.

68
00:04:08,771 --> 00:04:09,855
I can't.

69
00:04:09,938 --> 00:04:11,273
Please forgive me.

70
00:04:11,356 --> 00:04:12,900
I really can't delete it.

71
00:04:12,983 --> 00:04:15,319
I'm really sorry. It was a mistake,
but I can't delete it.

72
00:04:15,903 --> 00:04:17,529
You base your characters on your teachers

73
00:04:17,613 --> 00:04:20,866
and even have them say things
I can't even bring myself to say.

74
00:04:20,949 --> 00:04:22,076
How can I let that slide?

75
00:04:22,159 --> 00:04:23,535
Put yourself in my position.

76
00:04:24,828 --> 00:04:25,704
Even so.

77
00:04:26,914 --> 00:04:28,165
I can't delete it.

78
00:04:28,832 --> 00:04:29,958
I really can't.

79
00:04:31,502 --> 00:04:32,336
Fine.

80
00:04:34,338 --> 00:04:35,255
Then I will.

81
00:04:39,635 --> 00:04:40,928
PASSWORD

82
00:04:45,432 --> 00:04:46,642
Enter your password.

83
00:04:48,685 --> 00:04:49,645
Mr. Ga.

84
00:04:49,728 --> 00:04:53,273
I'll study really hard.

85
00:04:53,357 --> 00:04:55,943
I'll study math really hard.

86
00:04:56,026 --> 00:04:57,277
Please, give me a break.

87
00:04:57,361 --> 00:04:58,946
Even the dying get one last wish.

88
00:04:59,029 --> 00:05:02,074
Can't you do one favor
to help out a pitiful student?

89
00:05:02,157 --> 00:05:04,451
I put my life and soul into writing it.

90
00:05:04,535 --> 00:05:06,411
How can I just delete it?

91
00:05:07,246 --> 00:05:09,123
Please cut me a break.

92
00:05:10,415 --> 00:05:12,626
I really can't delete it.

93
00:05:13,836 --> 00:05:16,588
I can't delete it.

94
00:05:17,089 --> 00:05:18,590
Please.

95
00:05:20,425 --> 00:05:23,053
What am I going to do?

96
00:05:26,306 --> 00:05:27,599
I'm so sorry.

97
00:05:35,315 --> 00:05:37,192
30 MINUTES LATER

98
00:05:51,874 --> 00:05:53,000
If you really can't delete it,

99
00:05:56,670 --> 00:05:58,005
bring your parents to see me.

100
00:05:59,548 --> 00:06:00,591
-Sorry?
-If you're okay

101
00:06:00,674 --> 00:06:02,176
with your parents, the principal,

102
00:06:02,259 --> 00:06:04,845
the faculty and all the students
knowing what you've been up to.

103
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:06,722
No, sir.

104
00:06:06,805 --> 00:06:08,182
My mom will kill me.

105
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,643
It seems you know
what you've done is wrong.

106
00:06:14,188 --> 00:06:17,232
Why do you want to keep doing something
you can't tell anyone about?

107
00:06:19,610 --> 00:06:22,487
I'm going to check tomorrow,
so either delete it or bring your parents.

108
00:06:24,948 --> 00:06:26,158
Sir!

109
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:46,345
CHAPTER 20: THE OBSESSIVE TOP DOESN'T EVEN
HAVE A TOILET IN HIS BATHROOM

110
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:00,484
I'm home.

111
00:07:02,486 --> 00:07:03,862
I made galbijjim.

112
00:07:05,614 --> 00:07:06,865
I'm not hungry.

113
00:07:08,325 --> 00:07:10,577
What's wrong? Are you sick?

114
00:07:11,703 --> 00:07:12,621
No.

115
00:07:13,789 --> 00:07:16,750
Shall I make you tteokbokki instead?

116
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,085
I'm fine.

117
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:27,261
Shall I delete it?

118
00:07:30,097 --> 00:07:30,973
No, I can't.

119
00:07:32,724 --> 00:07:34,851
Then everyone will find out what I wrote.

120
00:07:34,935 --> 00:07:38,605
Still, isn't that better than deleting it?

121
00:07:39,940 --> 00:07:42,943
Am I crazy? It's better to delete it.

122
00:07:55,372 --> 00:07:56,873
-You're home?
-Yeah.

123
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,419
-Hey.
-Hey.

124
00:08:08,885 --> 00:08:12,931
Tae-ha caressed Yoon's snow-white skin…

125
00:08:15,475 --> 00:08:16,852
tenderly.

126
00:08:20,564 --> 00:08:22,733
Hey! Sit apart.

127
00:08:23,608 --> 00:08:24,776
I said sit apart.

128
00:08:25,569 --> 00:08:27,154
-What's wrong?
-You startled me.

129
00:08:28,572 --> 00:08:29,448
Wanna play?

130
00:08:30,073 --> 00:08:31,283
No, I can't.

131
00:08:31,366 --> 00:08:33,285
-Just one round.
-No, I need to get to bed.

132
00:08:33,368 --> 00:08:35,120
I know you want to.

133
00:08:35,203 --> 00:08:36,330
Just a quickie.

134
00:08:36,913 --> 00:08:38,040
Wanna

135
00:08:38,123 --> 00:08:41,376
-play?
-Just a quickie.

136
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:50,886
Let me join in.

137
00:08:50,969 --> 00:08:52,763
-The three of us?
-Move.

138
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:55,098
Was it leg day today? Nice.

139
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:57,309
No.

140
00:08:58,018 --> 00:08:59,561
Not two of you, nor three of you.

141
00:09:00,228 --> 00:09:01,480
Just play by yourself.

142
00:09:03,774 --> 00:09:05,233
What do you mean play by ourselves?

143
00:09:05,317 --> 00:09:07,277
What's wrong with you?

144
00:09:08,403 --> 00:09:10,614
You want to play too?
We can change partners.

145
00:09:10,697 --> 00:09:11,990
I'm disgusting.

146
00:09:13,116 --> 00:09:14,576
My mind. My imagination.

147
00:09:16,078 --> 00:09:17,704
What on earth was all that?

148
00:09:28,715 --> 00:09:29,800
BOYS' LOVE

149
00:09:29,883 --> 00:09:32,886
This is for all teachers and students.

150
00:09:32,969 --> 00:09:35,347
Just to inform you
that eleventh-grader Yeo Eui-ju

151
00:09:35,430 --> 00:09:40,977
has been writing a BL web novel
titled We Were Friends.

152
00:09:42,521 --> 00:09:43,855
BL?

153
00:09:43,939 --> 00:09:46,775
You told me you didn't like that.
Were you lying?

154
00:09:46,858 --> 00:09:47,943
Go-ya!

155
00:09:48,026 --> 00:09:49,152
Disgusting.

156
00:09:49,736 --> 00:09:51,696
Pretending to be all sweet and innocent.

157
00:09:52,197 --> 00:09:53,698
Why pair a guy with another guy?

158
00:09:54,282 --> 00:09:55,575
-No.
-Eui-ju.

159
00:09:58,620 --> 00:09:59,496
Mom.

160
00:10:00,747 --> 00:10:01,915
What's wrong?

161
00:10:02,499 --> 00:10:03,333
Mom, I…

162
00:10:07,504 --> 00:10:09,881
This is a crime.

163
00:10:09,965 --> 00:10:12,426
You've tarnished my name and my honor.

164
00:10:12,509 --> 00:10:14,302
I hope you rot in jail.

165
00:10:14,386 --> 00:10:15,679
I made a mistake.

166
00:10:16,513 --> 00:10:17,514
Are you crazy?

167
00:10:18,140 --> 00:10:20,183
Idle hands are the devil's playthings.

168
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:21,309
It gives me the creeps.

169
00:10:21,893 --> 00:10:22,936
Eui-ju.

170
00:10:23,937 --> 00:10:25,480
No.

171
00:10:25,564 --> 00:10:26,773
No, sir.

172
00:10:26,857 --> 00:10:28,066
It's not like that.

173
00:10:33,238 --> 00:10:34,531
I'm sorry.

174
00:10:34,614 --> 00:10:35,699
I'm sorry.

175
00:10:35,782 --> 00:10:38,076
My daughter didn't do anything wrong.

176
00:10:38,702 --> 00:10:40,871
She learned from me.

177
00:10:40,954 --> 00:10:42,956
-It's all my fault.
-Dad…

178
00:10:52,174 --> 00:10:53,675
No!

179
00:10:53,758 --> 00:10:55,927
What's this?

180
00:10:57,053 --> 00:10:58,388
Let me go!

181
00:11:00,849 --> 00:11:03,393
Don't come any closer.

182
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:12,819
No.

183
00:11:14,112 --> 00:11:15,197
No.

184
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,324
I must never be outed.

185
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,577
It seems you know
what you've done is wrong.

186
00:11:21,244 --> 00:11:23,914
Why do you want to keep doing something
you can't tell anyone about?

187
00:11:29,252 --> 00:11:31,087
Boys' love…

188
00:11:31,171 --> 00:11:35,091
"The character with the biggest fan base
is the obsessive exhibitionist."

189
00:11:35,884 --> 00:11:39,513
"He lives in a marble penthouse
where the lights are always off."

190
00:11:41,806 --> 00:11:44,768
"He's cut ties with his family
and has no friends."

191
00:11:45,685 --> 00:11:47,938
"When he showers,
he only ever uses the rain shower head."

192
00:11:48,855 --> 00:11:50,732
"In his bathroom, there's…"

193
00:11:52,025 --> 00:11:53,026
NO TOILET

194
00:11:53,610 --> 00:11:54,444
"…no toilet?"

195
00:11:57,239 --> 00:11:58,073
Why not?

196
00:12:02,035 --> 00:12:03,870
Why did I have to get caught

197
00:12:03,954 --> 00:12:06,248
by that asshole of a math teacher?

198
00:12:11,711 --> 00:12:16,675
Ga Woo-su!

199
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:25,976
Good morning.

200
00:12:34,317 --> 00:12:35,318
Follow me.

201
00:12:41,825 --> 00:12:44,744
COUNSELING IN PROGRESS

202
00:12:44,828 --> 00:12:45,870
Did you delete it?

203
00:12:51,876 --> 00:12:53,044
Mr. Ga.

204
00:12:53,545 --> 00:12:57,549
I started writing web novels
when I was in eighth grade.

205
00:13:00,176 --> 00:13:01,261
And?

206
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:06,891
It was just a crappy story I made by
cobbling together bits and pieces I liked.

207
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:11,896
But I decided to upload it
to the Challenge League.

208
00:13:11,980 --> 00:13:13,898
Then, out of the blue, it got

209
00:13:13,982 --> 00:13:14,983
two favorites.

210
00:13:15,066 --> 00:13:18,153
I got so excited that
I did a mass release of two more episodes.

211
00:13:20,655 --> 00:13:22,949
What I mean by that

212
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,868
is in quick succession.

213
00:13:24,951 --> 00:13:28,663
You have to be quick with
the first few episodes to generate

214
00:13:28,747 --> 00:13:29,831
a buzz.

215
00:13:29,914 --> 00:13:32,250
Anyhow, the number of favorites

216
00:13:32,334 --> 00:13:33,793
went straight back down to one.

217
00:13:33,877 --> 00:13:35,503
They must have seen the next two episodes

218
00:13:36,713 --> 00:13:37,547
and done a runner.

219
00:13:37,631 --> 00:13:39,507
10 MINUTES LATER

220
00:13:40,508 --> 00:13:42,927
These days, do you know what I think

221
00:13:43,011 --> 00:13:44,471
when I wake up in the morning?

222
00:13:46,348 --> 00:13:48,475
I can see the light
at the end of the tunnel.

223
00:13:48,558 --> 00:13:52,354
What I thought was a dead-end cave
was actually a tunnel.

224
00:13:52,979 --> 00:13:56,066
The cold and lonely winter

225
00:13:57,150 --> 00:14:00,153
is finally coming to an end
and flowers are going to bloom.

226
00:14:01,821 --> 00:14:05,283
Mr. Ga, this novel

227
00:14:05,367 --> 00:14:08,953
gives me hope
and is a dream I can't give up.

228
00:14:09,037 --> 00:14:11,748
Can you please help me
make my dream come true?

229
00:14:11,831 --> 00:14:14,084
Can you please help me finish my novel?

230
00:14:15,293 --> 00:14:16,127
No.

231
00:14:17,128 --> 00:14:18,046
Just this once.

232
00:14:18,129 --> 00:14:19,631
Just this once, please.

233
00:14:21,007 --> 00:14:24,219
Are you saying you intend to keep writing
the sort of things I would never say?

234
00:14:24,302 --> 00:14:27,097
The sort of stuff that gives me the ick
and sets my teeth on edge?

235
00:14:31,768 --> 00:14:32,644
Are you crying?

236
00:14:32,727 --> 00:14:33,770
No, sir.

237
00:14:34,938 --> 00:14:37,357
I know I did wrong.

238
00:14:38,566 --> 00:14:42,195
But how can I delete it?
It's got more than 20,000 favorites.

239
00:14:43,947 --> 00:14:46,866
Anyone would think I'm the bad guy here.
I'm the victim!

240
00:14:47,492 --> 00:14:49,160
Of all the different genres,

241
00:14:50,870 --> 00:14:52,539
why did it have to be BL?

242
00:14:53,331 --> 00:14:57,585
Because the more I heard "No, no,"
the more I want to encourage them,

243
00:14:57,669 --> 00:15:01,381
and even just the slightest brush
of a fingertip creates a deep yearning.

244
00:15:03,591 --> 00:15:05,301
Do you even know what you did wrong?

245
00:15:05,969 --> 00:15:06,886
Yes, I do.

246
00:15:07,929 --> 00:15:09,013
I do know.

247
00:15:09,806 --> 00:15:12,892
But if you look at it from a more worldly
point-of-view, love is love.

248
00:15:12,976 --> 00:15:15,729
When two people love each other,
gender isn't that important.

249
00:15:15,812 --> 00:15:17,105
Not that.

250
00:15:18,565 --> 00:15:20,316
Not that?

251
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,068
Then, the raunchiness?

252
00:15:22,152 --> 00:15:23,987
But it's not even rated 15.

253
00:15:24,070 --> 00:15:26,156
Even the publisher said it's mild.

254
00:15:26,239 --> 00:15:27,198
Mild!

255
00:15:29,075 --> 00:15:29,909
Not that either?

256
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:34,372
Making my teachers the main characters?

257
00:15:34,456 --> 00:15:37,125
Yes, that was a huge mistake on my part.

258
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:38,793
And I'm really sorry about that, but--

259
00:15:38,877 --> 00:15:40,670
You really are a lost cause.

260
00:15:43,381 --> 00:15:45,383
You still don't know what you did wrong.

261
00:15:45,467 --> 00:15:47,135
How can you not know?

262
00:15:47,218 --> 00:15:48,052
I'm sorry.

263
00:15:48,136 --> 00:15:49,262
I just don't get it.

264
00:15:50,972 --> 00:15:52,098
How is it?

265
00:15:53,057 --> 00:15:54,100
Why on earth…

266
00:15:56,394 --> 00:15:57,854
Am I not the main character?

267
00:16:01,399 --> 00:16:02,233
Sorry?

268
00:16:03,693 --> 00:16:06,112
You're going to have Dong-ju and Gi-jeon
end up together.

269
00:16:06,196 --> 00:16:07,238
Where does that leave me?

270
00:16:09,699 --> 00:16:11,201
You're a sub character.

271
00:16:12,535 --> 00:16:13,453
A sub.

272
00:16:16,039 --> 00:16:18,082
I've never been a sub my whole life.

273
00:16:19,959 --> 00:16:20,960
Sorry?

274
00:16:21,586 --> 00:16:22,962
I want you to rewrite it.

275
00:16:23,046 --> 00:16:24,214
With me

276
00:16:25,256 --> 00:16:26,132
as the main character.

277
00:16:28,676 --> 00:16:30,512
-What?
-You know what the main character is.

278
00:16:32,180 --> 00:16:34,140
You want to be the obsessive top?

279
00:16:36,392 --> 00:16:37,644
If that's the main character.

280
00:16:40,814 --> 00:16:42,774
Then the story will go off the rails.

281
00:16:42,857 --> 00:16:44,609
I don't care if it jumps the shark,

282
00:16:44,692 --> 00:16:46,903
just know that I'm going to check
each and every episode.

283
00:16:48,780 --> 00:16:51,866
Sir, you can't check it in advance.
I simply can't allow it.

284
00:16:53,576 --> 00:16:54,786
Why not?

285
00:16:54,869 --> 00:16:55,829
Well…

286
00:16:56,996 --> 00:16:59,999
If I know you're going to be reading,

287
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:02,085
how can I write that kind of stuff?

288
00:17:02,168 --> 00:17:03,294
Then delete it.

289
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,180
You have two choices.

290
00:17:14,264 --> 00:17:16,182
Delete it or let me check each episode.

291
00:17:16,266 --> 00:17:17,600
What are you going to do?

292
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:23,398
I'll do it.

293
00:17:23,481 --> 00:17:25,066
I'll let you check it.

294
00:17:30,947 --> 00:17:32,115
What am I going to do?

295
00:17:45,003 --> 00:17:47,046
So he's mad, not because it's BL,

296
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:49,841
but because he isn't the main character?

297
00:17:52,260 --> 00:17:54,262
He's not normal.

298
00:17:54,888 --> 00:17:57,348
He must be crazy.

299
00:17:57,432 --> 00:17:59,183
EBC FILMING PROPOSAL

300
00:17:59,267 --> 00:18:00,935
CHAPTER 21:
YOU REALLY THINK WOO-SU WILL DO IT?

301
00:18:03,021 --> 00:18:04,397
3. OBJECTIVE

302
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:07,400
Come in.

303
00:18:08,735 --> 00:18:10,570
Do come in.

304
00:18:11,070 --> 00:18:12,447
Have a seat.

305
00:18:15,491 --> 00:18:16,367
Take a look.

306
00:18:19,704 --> 00:18:22,707
EBC is coming here to film?

307
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:24,125
Finally.

308
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:27,170
Next Monday,
the makers of that hit program

309
00:18:27,253 --> 00:18:30,173
are coming to film at our school.

310
00:18:33,509 --> 00:18:36,804
You four teachers
are the pride of our school.

311
00:18:36,888 --> 00:18:39,432
You're all elite teachers
with impressive resumes.

312
00:18:39,515 --> 00:18:44,687
When you're filmed teaching the kids
with your endless passion and dedication,

313
00:18:44,771 --> 00:18:48,441
the foundation's donors are sure
to start writing checks, right, Dong-ju?

314
00:18:48,524 --> 00:18:50,234
Sorry? Me?

315
00:18:50,318 --> 00:18:53,279
I want you to write an essay
setting out your philosophy of education.

316
00:18:53,363 --> 00:18:55,281
One that elicits emotion.

317
00:18:55,365 --> 00:18:57,617
Enough to make people cry.

318
00:18:58,618 --> 00:19:00,244
Yes, ma'am.

319
00:19:01,245 --> 00:19:02,622
And as for you, Gi-jeon.

320
00:19:02,705 --> 00:19:04,457
Prepare a few words about your path

321
00:19:04,540 --> 00:19:07,335
from retiring as a professional athlete
to become a teacher.

322
00:19:07,418 --> 00:19:09,545
Yes, ma'am.

323
00:19:09,629 --> 00:19:12,590
-Next, Da-ju.
-Yes.

324
00:19:12,674 --> 00:19:14,550
Do you think you can rehash

325
00:19:14,634 --> 00:19:16,970
your TUD talk?

326
00:19:17,053 --> 00:19:21,057
Your grand vision
is sure to go down in history.

327
00:19:21,641 --> 00:19:23,810
-Down in history.
-Down in history.

328
00:19:24,644 --> 00:19:27,522
And last but not least, Woo-su.

329
00:19:27,605 --> 00:19:29,774
What more needs to be said?

330
00:19:29,857 --> 00:19:32,276
You're the very definition
of a global elite.

331
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:36,072
We just need to change your glasses.

332
00:19:37,198 --> 00:19:39,450
-And in class--
-I won't be taking part.

333
00:19:41,828 --> 00:19:43,037
Sorry?

334
00:19:45,289 --> 00:19:46,666
I don't want to film.

335
00:19:46,749 --> 00:19:49,502
But I'll cooperate in another way
if there's any.

336
00:19:50,712 --> 00:19:51,879
Woo-su.

337
00:19:53,506 --> 00:19:54,841
I guess you didn't hear me.

338
00:19:58,928 --> 00:20:01,055
This program will be on EBC.

339
00:20:01,639 --> 00:20:04,851
If you don't agree to film,

340
00:20:04,934 --> 00:20:06,602
that's going to be a problem.

341
00:20:07,186 --> 00:20:08,062
I'm sorry.

342
00:20:08,688 --> 00:20:09,689
That won't be possible.

343
00:20:12,358 --> 00:20:14,527
Still, for the sake of
the school's future development,

344
00:20:14,610 --> 00:20:16,487
please take some time to reconsider.

345
00:20:16,571 --> 00:20:18,197
I believe I've made myself clear.

346
00:20:18,281 --> 00:20:20,408
If you've nothing more to say,
I'll be on my way.

347
00:20:27,290 --> 00:20:28,708
Don't worry, Ms. Kim.

348
00:20:29,459 --> 00:20:30,793
I'll convince him.

349
00:20:31,502 --> 00:20:32,962
Da-ju.

350
00:20:34,589 --> 00:20:35,882
If you wouldn't mind.

351
00:20:37,008 --> 00:20:38,968
I want the four of you

352
00:20:39,052 --> 00:20:41,345
including Woo-su to be on camera.

353
00:20:42,638 --> 00:20:45,641
There's a week until filming,
I'm sure you can do it.

354
00:20:46,726 --> 00:20:48,311
-Yes.
-Of course.

355
00:20:48,895 --> 00:20:49,937
Don't worry.

356
00:20:56,444 --> 00:20:57,570
What are you going to do?

357
00:20:58,196 --> 00:20:59,363
Got any ideas?

358
00:21:00,448 --> 00:21:01,407
Of course, he doesn't.

359
00:21:02,617 --> 00:21:04,243
Couldn't just the three of us do it?

360
00:21:04,327 --> 00:21:06,412
You heard what the principal said.

361
00:21:07,872 --> 00:21:09,540
There's no point without Woo-su.

362
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:13,419
We're basically Ga Woo-su and Boys.

363
00:21:14,003 --> 00:21:16,255
You really think Woo-su will do it?

364
00:21:16,339 --> 00:21:18,508
You know him better than anyone.

365
00:21:18,591 --> 00:21:20,426
Why did you say you'd convince him?

366
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:22,261
At this school,

367
00:21:22,345 --> 00:21:25,473
upsetting the principal

368
00:21:25,556 --> 00:21:27,683
is a fate worse than death.

369
00:21:28,476 --> 00:21:29,644
If Woo-su won't film,

370
00:21:30,978 --> 00:21:32,313
we'll all end up being fired.

371
00:21:33,856 --> 00:21:35,108
No way.

372
00:21:36,818 --> 00:21:37,860
You think?

373
00:21:43,950 --> 00:21:46,202
Hey, Woo-su.

374
00:21:46,285 --> 00:21:47,203
Not doing it.

375
00:21:47,787 --> 00:21:49,080
Just this once.

376
00:21:49,163 --> 00:21:50,498
It'll be over in no time.

377
00:21:52,834 --> 00:21:54,127
How can you even say that?

378
00:21:54,210 --> 00:21:55,503
You of all people.

379
00:21:55,586 --> 00:21:57,088
You think I want to do this?

380
00:21:57,171 --> 00:21:59,382
I've known you since third grade.

381
00:22:00,007 --> 00:22:01,717
I know what happened better than anyone.

382
00:22:01,801 --> 00:22:03,427
Then don't make me say it again.

383
00:22:03,511 --> 00:22:04,345
Get out.

384
00:22:05,429 --> 00:22:07,682
Woo-su, don't make me
get down on my knees and beg.

385
00:22:07,765 --> 00:22:09,684
Don't bother. Now get out.

386
00:22:11,936 --> 00:22:12,812
Fine.

387
00:22:27,326 --> 00:22:28,202
WE WERE FRIENDS

388
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:37,420
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 3

389
00:22:38,379 --> 00:22:40,173
When is she going to upload episode four?

390
00:22:42,884 --> 00:22:46,387
CHAPTER 22: DO I REALLY HAVE TO CHANGE
THIS FOR YOU TO FEEL VALIDATED?

391
00:22:46,971 --> 00:22:48,514
Now that he's going to check my work,

392
00:22:48,598 --> 00:22:51,267
how am I supposed to write
all the flirty stuff?

393
00:22:55,313 --> 00:22:57,106
I refuse to breathe
until we get episode four!

394
00:22:57,190 --> 00:22:58,941
Do you feel the tension between these two?

395
00:22:59,025 --> 00:23:00,735
Hurry up and upload episode four!

396
00:23:00,818 --> 00:23:02,820
When is episode four coming out?

397
00:23:26,427 --> 00:23:27,428
Where's episode four?

398
00:23:28,971 --> 00:23:31,599
Where's the "mass release"?
Have you lost your spark?

399
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:34,060
I'm sorry, sir.

400
00:23:34,143 --> 00:23:35,645
There's no need to apologize to me.

401
00:23:37,063 --> 00:23:38,940
Try to understand how Si-on feels.

402
00:23:39,023 --> 00:23:40,566
What he likes and how he grew up.

403
00:23:40,650 --> 00:23:43,861
What he thinks about Yoon.

404
00:23:43,945 --> 00:23:45,571
Concentrate on Si-on.

405
00:23:58,334 --> 00:23:59,794
I hear EBC is gonna film at school.

406
00:23:59,877 --> 00:24:02,296
I hope Dong-ju doesn't become famous.

407
00:24:06,259 --> 00:24:07,551
Where are you going?

408
00:24:32,576 --> 00:24:33,536
MATHEMATICS

409
00:24:41,127 --> 00:24:43,963
Why do you get nervous and run away
every time you see Mr. Ga?

410
00:24:45,131 --> 00:24:46,590
Me?

411
00:24:46,674 --> 00:24:47,508
What do you mean?

412
00:24:48,134 --> 00:24:49,218
No, I don't.

413
00:24:54,765 --> 00:24:57,310
-Where did we get to?
-We're up to page 101.

414
00:24:57,393 --> 00:24:58,227
Page 101.

415
00:24:59,020 --> 00:25:00,730
Velocity and acceleration.

416
00:25:06,902 --> 00:25:08,404
He's so hardcore.

417
00:25:08,487 --> 00:25:10,948
How can he ride her like that
just for getting four points?

418
00:25:11,032 --> 00:25:12,325
A lot of kids gave up on math.

419
00:25:12,408 --> 00:25:14,410
But Eui-ju's the only one
that took the bait.

420
00:25:15,828 --> 00:25:18,748
It's not just the after-school class.
She seems to be really stressed.

421
00:25:26,839 --> 00:25:30,009
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

422
00:25:31,302 --> 00:25:35,139
THE DOOR TO THE PENTHOUSE OPENS
TO REVEAL A LONG CORRIDOR

423
00:25:37,558 --> 00:25:41,937
HIS HAND CLUTCHING THE STRAP ON HIS BAG,
YOON APPROACHES TAE-HA

424
00:25:42,021 --> 00:25:44,106
I told you not to be late.
Not even a second.

425
00:25:45,191 --> 00:25:46,025
I'm sorry.

426
00:25:46,525 --> 00:25:47,860
I ran here so as not to be late.

427
00:25:47,943 --> 00:25:49,362
Were you with Si-on?

428
00:25:50,446 --> 00:25:53,032
YOON COULDN'T BRING HIMSELF TO ANSWER

429
00:25:53,115 --> 00:25:55,284
HIS SILENCE WAS ENOUGH OF AN ANSWER

430
00:25:58,871 --> 00:25:59,830
This won't do.

431
00:26:00,456 --> 00:26:01,332
Choi Yoon.

432
00:26:02,625 --> 00:26:04,126
This place is huge.

433
00:26:04,210 --> 00:26:05,461
You live here alone?

434
00:26:07,338 --> 00:26:08,756
What about that ten million?

435
00:26:09,507 --> 00:26:11,509
Why are you being like this, Tae-ha?

436
00:26:12,802 --> 00:26:14,136
This isn't you.

437
00:26:16,931 --> 00:26:19,600
I'm not the same guy
who hung on your every word.

438
00:26:20,976 --> 00:26:23,396
I'm not the same guy
who ran to you like a puppy.

439
00:26:24,730 --> 00:26:25,689
Not anymore.

440
00:26:26,649 --> 00:26:27,942
Tae-ha.

441
00:26:28,025 --> 00:26:28,859
No.

442
00:26:31,028 --> 00:26:31,862
I could be

443
00:26:32,738 --> 00:26:33,614
your puppy.

444
00:26:34,990 --> 00:26:35,950
From now on,

445
00:26:36,951 --> 00:26:39,120
I'll be your personal bitch.

446
00:26:41,038 --> 00:26:43,582
FROM NOW ON, I'LL BE YOUR PERSONAL BITCH

447
00:26:48,921 --> 00:26:51,924
I made the right choice.

448
00:26:52,007 --> 00:26:53,676
This is better than deleting it.

449
00:26:54,468 --> 00:26:56,762
When faced with a difficult choice,

450
00:26:56,846 --> 00:26:58,764
taking the more difficult path

451
00:26:58,848 --> 00:27:00,266
is the way to salvation.

452
00:27:00,349 --> 00:27:02,935
No, I'm dying here.

453
00:27:16,824 --> 00:27:18,200
If it's the penthouse,

454
00:27:18,826 --> 00:27:20,578
shouldn't that be where Si-on lives?

455
00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:22,746
Sorry?

456
00:27:24,165 --> 00:27:24,999
What did I say?

457
00:27:26,625 --> 00:27:29,670
Si-on should be the main character.

458
00:27:29,753 --> 00:27:30,713
Again.

459
00:27:31,380 --> 00:27:33,507
Si-on should be the main character.

460
00:27:33,591 --> 00:27:34,592
Right. From now on,

461
00:27:34,675 --> 00:27:37,052
Si-on is the obsessive lead
and Tae-ha the regretful sub.

462
00:27:37,136 --> 00:27:40,055
Give all the key impactful lines to Si-on.

463
00:27:40,139 --> 00:27:41,849
Rewrite it with Tae-ha's role minimized.

464
00:27:46,604 --> 00:27:47,438
Now.

465
00:27:49,732 --> 00:27:51,066
Here?

466
00:27:53,068 --> 00:27:54,069
You've got one hour.

467
00:28:00,075 --> 00:28:00,951
Get away from him.

468
00:28:03,412 --> 00:28:04,330
What?

469
00:28:09,335 --> 00:28:11,462
It can't be helped
if you've got feelings for Tae-ha.

470
00:28:11,545 --> 00:28:13,255
But I won't stand idly by.

471
00:28:13,339 --> 00:28:14,256
From now on,

472
00:28:15,090 --> 00:28:17,718
I'll be your personal bitch.

473
00:28:21,764 --> 00:28:23,224
Hang on a second.

474
00:28:23,307 --> 00:28:24,183
This feels wrong.

475
00:28:27,478 --> 00:28:28,354
Sorry?

476
00:28:31,273 --> 00:28:33,192
What's wrong?

477
00:28:33,275 --> 00:28:36,111
Shouldn't this be Tae-ha's line?

478
00:28:40,282 --> 00:28:43,160
I know it feels a little awkward.

479
00:28:44,411 --> 00:28:45,579
Still, let's stick with it.

480
00:28:45,663 --> 00:28:48,582
Yoon needs to realize Si-on isn't the one.

481
00:28:48,666 --> 00:28:50,751
This isn't the first time
he's been gaslit.

482
00:28:51,377 --> 00:28:52,962
It's really frustrating.

483
00:28:53,045 --> 00:28:57,174
That needs to happen for Si-on to go
tumbling head over heels in misery.

484
00:28:57,258 --> 00:29:00,177
At this rate,
he won't even manage a single roly-poly.

485
00:29:00,261 --> 00:29:02,012
But, more than that,

486
00:29:03,264 --> 00:29:04,390
aren't I the lead character?

487
00:29:05,015 --> 00:29:07,476
Right now, Si-on is coming across
as the obsessive top.

488
00:29:11,605 --> 00:29:12,856
Not at all.

489
00:29:12,940 --> 00:29:15,943
No way. Of course not.

490
00:29:17,945 --> 00:29:20,447
It's just, as I was writing it,

491
00:29:20,531 --> 00:29:23,909
I felt like I should change
the flow of the narrative.

492
00:29:24,410 --> 00:29:26,412
In that way, how can I put it…

493
00:29:26,495 --> 00:29:29,081
The characters will go through
a wider range of emotions,

494
00:29:29,164 --> 00:29:31,292
and the story itself will be more diverse.

495
00:29:32,334 --> 00:29:33,335
But the thing is…

496
00:29:34,336 --> 00:29:35,337
Just a moment.

497
00:29:42,052 --> 00:29:44,888
Do I really have to change this
for you to feel validated?

498
00:29:55,524 --> 00:29:56,567
Fine.

499
00:29:57,484 --> 00:29:59,528
You're doing great.

500
00:29:59,612 --> 00:30:01,155
Fine, now if everybody

501
00:30:01,238 --> 00:30:03,282
can just hang in there!

502
00:30:04,283 --> 00:30:05,784
-Let's get back to it.
-Okay.

503
00:30:05,868 --> 00:30:07,745
-Let's do this.
-From the top.

504
00:30:07,828 --> 00:30:09,663
I'm fine with that.

505
00:30:10,831 --> 00:30:12,916
-We're doing this again?
-From now on,

506
00:30:13,876 --> 00:30:15,919
I'm going to be your personal bitch.

507
00:30:23,135 --> 00:30:24,303
Is this right?

508
00:30:24,386 --> 00:30:28,015
What the heck? I can't even write
my own novel how I want.

509
00:30:31,477 --> 00:30:32,603
Hang on.

510
00:30:33,604 --> 00:30:35,856
He's only checking the original file.

511
00:30:39,234 --> 00:30:40,694
That's much better.

512
00:30:40,778 --> 00:30:42,237
Really?

513
00:30:42,321 --> 00:30:43,155
Upload it.

514
00:30:55,459 --> 00:30:58,045
WE WERE FRIENDS
EPISODE 4 REAL

515
00:31:00,547 --> 00:31:01,382
EPISODE 4 REAL

516
00:31:02,049 --> 00:31:02,925
WE WERE FRIENDS

517
00:31:07,721 --> 00:31:08,681
SUBMIT A NEW PROJECT

518
00:31:11,725 --> 00:31:13,477
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

519
00:31:30,119 --> 00:31:33,539
There's no way he'll check online.

520
00:31:33,622 --> 00:31:35,165
Like he'd ever look up We Were Friends.

521
00:31:35,749 --> 00:31:36,875
-Not him.
-You little…

522
00:31:36,959 --> 00:31:38,168
Today's the day.

523
00:31:38,252 --> 00:31:39,420
Check your students' uniforms

524
00:31:39,503 --> 00:31:40,963
and make sure
they're on their best behavior.

525
00:31:41,046 --> 00:31:43,340
Let's make sure this is a success.

526
00:31:43,424 --> 00:31:45,217
-What's going on?
-Film him on the sly?

527
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:47,010
I'll keep it a secret.

528
00:31:47,094 --> 00:31:48,178
I know everything.

529
00:31:48,262 --> 00:31:51,265
If you're not going to cooperate,
you leave me no choice.

530
00:31:51,348 --> 00:31:53,559
Why are you going this far?
You're going to regret this.

531
00:31:53,642 --> 00:31:55,310
Are you going to betray my trust?

532
00:31:55,394 --> 00:31:56,645
-I'll figure it out by myself.
-Try that, then.

533
00:31:56,729 --> 00:31:59,857
What am I going to do now, Mr. Ga?

534
00:31:59,940 --> 00:32:01,942
Shall I just transfer?

535
00:32:58,081 --> 00:33:00,083
Subtitle: Paul Carver
